                " \nCOMMISSION FOR CONCILIATION, MEDIATION AND ARBITRATION (CCMA)\n ",
                " \n \nACCOUNTANT: EXPENDITURE MANAGEMENT\nNational Office\nRef: AEMNO10-23\nPost level: 07\n \nThe National Office has a vacancy for an Accountant: Expenditure Management.\n\nPurpose: To execute the accounts payable process and procedures in order to ensure timeous payments of suppliers and service providers in compliance with internal financial policies and the PMFA.\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 Accounts Payable Maintenance\n\u2022 Cash Flow Management\n\u2022 Internal Control and Risk Management\n\u2022 Team Supervision\n\nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 3-year National Diploma in Accounting\n\u2022 3 years\u2019 General Accounting Experience\n\n\nClosing date: 26 October 2023\n\n\nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copies of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to:recruitment@ccma.org.za. \n\n\u201cWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: AEMNO10-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. And that the application is sent to the email address contained herein. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified.\u201d\n \nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representivity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts. Preference will be given to candidate from the designated groups.\n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nCASE MANAGEMENT OFFICER\nWestern Cape Province \u2013 Cape Town Office\nREF: CMOWCCO10-23\nPost level: 09\n \nThe Western Cape Province \u2013 Cape Town Office has a vacancy of Case Management Officer.\n \nPurpose\nTo effectively and efficiently handle queries and assist the public with regard to appropriate processing procedures, screening of cases in terms of relevant legislation and CCMA guidelines.\n \nKey Performance Areas:-\n\u2022 Case Advice\n\u2022 Case Screening\n\u2022 Case Capturing\n\u2022 Schedule and screen documentation\n\u2022 Process outcome and finalise cases\n\u2022 Venue Administration\n\u2022 Pre-Conciliation\n \nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 Unless a candidate can demonstrate suitability through relevant experience of not less than three (3) years in Employment Laws, Trade Union  environment/Bargaining Council/Labour Inspector or Human Resources role, a Matric and Diploma in Labour Relations (or relevant equivalent) with one (1) year of practical experience will be required\n\u2022 One (1) to three (3) years relevant working experience in a case management service Employment Laws, Trade Union environment/Bargaining Council/Labour Inspector or Human Resources role\n\u2022 At least 2 African languages would be an advantage\n \n \nClosing date: 26 October 2023\n\nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copies of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to:recruitmentwc@ccma.org.za\n \nWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: CMOWCCO10-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. And that the application is sent to the email address contained herein. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified\u201d.\n \nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representativity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts. Preference will be given to candidate from the designated groups.",
                "GOVERNANCE OFFICER: GOVERNANCE AND SECRETARIAT SERVICES\nThe National Office has a vacancy for a Governance Officer: Governance and Secretariat Services\n \nPurpose: The Governance Officer of the CCMA is responsible for assisting in providing Corporate Governance services for the CCMA, Governance and Management Structures.\n \nKey Performance Areas (Include but not limited to):\n\n\u2022 Corporate Governance Advisory Services including the facilitation of performance evaluations for governance structures, implementation of the King IV Report on Corporate Governance, and the development and maintenance of the Corporate Governance Maturity Model and RoadMap.\n\u2022 Embedding the culture of good Corporate Governance\n\u2022 Ethics Management\n\u2022 Fraud Prevention and Anti \u2013 Corruption\n\u2022 Policy Management\n\u2022 Monthly and Quarterly Reporting\n \nKey Requirements:\n\u2022 Bachelor\u2019s degree or National Diploma: Public/Business Administration/ LLB (or relevant equivalent and a certificate in Corporate Governance from the Chartered Institute of Governance or Equivalent)\n\u2022 Minimum 3 to 5 years\u2019 experience in corporate governance and secretarial services\n\u2022 Sound and practical understanding of King IV Report on Corporate Governance\nSound knowledge of legislation and regulations pertaining to the environment e.g., LRA, PFMA, Treasury regulations, etc.\n\u2022 Sound and practical knowledge of Policy Development\n \n \nClosing date: 24 October 2023\n \nTo respond in confidence, please send your detailed CV, copies of your qualifications, and a covering letter disclosing information that will assist the panel in considering your application to:recruitment@ccma.org.za.\n \n\u201cWhen responding to the advert please ensure that the position reference Ref: GOGSS10-23 is quoted first on the subject line, as is. And that the application is sent to the email address contained herein. Failure to observe this protocol may result in your application being disqualified.\u201d\n \nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The CCMA reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the CCMA to promote representivity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of the posts. Preference will be given to candidate from the designated groups."
