                " \nFINANCIAL SECTOR CONDUCT AUTHORITY (FSCA)\n ",
                " \n \nANALYST - SUPERVISION: BANKS AND PAYMENT PROVIDERS DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA888\n \nPurpose of the Job:\nTo effectively regulate and supervise the Banks and Payment Providers, to protect the interest of consumers and to ensure a sound regulatory environment. The person appointed in this position will report to the Manager: Banks and Payment Providers.\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 Monitor compliance with legislation to ensure sound and efficient Financial Services Providers and the protection of consumers;\n\u2022 Analyse financial statements and compliance reports of Banks and Payment Providers;\n\u2022 Identify and report trends in the financial services sector with possible impact on the FSCA\u2019s regulatory objectives;\n\u2022 Conduct on-site and off-site inspections in terms of the risk-based supervision approach and report on the outcomes of such inspections;\n\u2022 Liaise with the Banks and Payment Providers industry stakeholders; and\n\u2022 Perform administrative or other activities relating to the supervision of the Banks and Payment Providers.\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nThe candidate must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: Problem analysis and solving, judgement, oral and written communication, information gathering; good interpersonal skills; the ability to work in a team; and emotional intelligence. Knowledge of a workflow system will be a strong recommendation. Good computer skills.\n\n\n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified.\n \nRequirements\nBachelor\u2019s degree in Commerce, Law or Banking and other relevant discipline with at least 2-3 years working experience within the financial services industry. The candidate must have a good knowledge and exposure to the financial sector, a good understanding of the Banks Act of 1990 and the Financial Sector Regulation act. \n \nClosing Date: 3 November 2023\n \nWork Level: Skilled\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nPROJECT MANAGER - PROJECT MANAGEMENT OFFICE: ICT DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA269\n \nPurpose of the Job: \nTo lead, oversee and ensure the successful delivery and management of single or multiple projects within scope, and specified constraints of time and cost to deliver business value. The person appointed will report to the Departmental Head: Project Management office (PMO).\n\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 Direct and coordinate activities of project personnel to ensure project progresses is on schedule and within scope and budget;\n\u2022 Review status reports prepared by project personnel, and modify schedules and plans as required;\n\u2022 Plan team resource needs; allocate, supervise and review work;\n\u2022 Prepare project status reports, and keep management, clients and others informed of project status and related issues; \n\u2022 Ensure budget requirements for projects are identified and submitted on time;\n\u2022 Work closely with business-units and ICT to understand and prioritise business goals and information needs; \n\u2022 Ensure the project governance is always adhered to for all projects\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nThe candidate must demonstrate the following skills and attributes:  Distinctive blend of business, IT, financial and communication skills, because this is a highly visible position with substantial impact, Effective influencing and negotiating skills in an environment where this role may not directly control resources, Good understanding of current and emerging technologies and how other enterprises are employing them to drive digital business, excellent oral and written communication skills, good presentation skills, be creative and innovative, quality and detail orientated, customer focused, excellent skills in establishing priorities, managing workload, a self-starter who can work independently, dependable and highly organised with business maturity, discretion, enthusiasm, and a positive attitude. Strategic thinking and leadership, with strong ability in stakeholder management, successfully developed and implemented new technology, work processes or process improvements; Good understanding of current and emerging technologies and how other enterprises are employing them to drive digital business. Strong computer skills including Microsoft Office\n\n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified.\n\n\nRequirements\nA Bachelor\u2019s or master\u2019s degree in computer science, information systems, business administration, or a related discipline with an information technology focus and a Project Management certification. Demonstrated experience in leading diverse teams, experience with one or more project management methodologies (e.g. PMI, PMBOK, PRINCE2 and Agile). The candidate must have a minimum of 5 - 8 years demonstrated project management experience encompassing the execution of complex or multiple systems development projects with 5 years of progressive broad-based information systems and business experience; digital platforms, experience in software and infrastructure engineering involving development and testing of applications. \n \nClosing Date: 3 November 2023\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDATA ENGINEER - ICT DATA AND ANALYTICS SERVICES DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA1044\n \nPurpose of the job:\n\nTo Design, build, expand, and optimize the data pipeline architecture, as well as optimize data flow and optimize the organization\u2019s data ingestion process to support data initiatives. The person appointed to this position will report to the Senior Specialist: ICT Data & Analytics.\n\nRequirements:\n\nKey Performance Area:\n\u2022 Develop, innovate and maintain the data architecture that will drive various initiatives/projects across the organisation\n\u2022 Collaborate with teams to build strategic data models that will help enable the achievement of business outcomes\n\u2022 Create robust and automated pipelines to ingest and process structured and unstructured data from source systems into analytical platforms\n\u2022 Conduct complex data analysis and report on results\n\u2022 Build and optimise \u2018big data\u2019 data pipelines, architectures and datasets\n\u2022 Build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency and workload management\n\u2022 Develop and maintain datasets\n\u2022 Analyse raw data and Interpret trends and patterns\n\u2022 Prepare data for prescriptive and predictive modelling\n\u2022 Reformulate existing frameworks to optimize functionality.\n\u2022 Deploy and schedule ETL jobs (Batch/Micro batch processing)\n\u2022 Partner with various stakeholders within the organisation to drive the improvement in the way that data is stored and consumed.\n\u2022 Support application team development by writing stored procedures, functions etc. \n\u2022 Develop and maintain data security and permissions, including data encryption and database user access controls and logging.\n\u2022 Build algorithms and prototypes.\n\u2022 Lead business stakeholder\u2019s engagement on Data Engineer standards and reporting requirements in order to derive the data driven strategy of the FSCA.\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nThe candidate must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: Must have extensive experience with ETL, technical expertise with data models, data mining, and segmentation techniques, experience using MS SSIS, MS SSAS, MS SSRS and Visual Studio data tools, advanced working SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, dimensional modeling, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of other databases, experience performing root cause analysis on internal and external data and processes to answer specific business questions and identify opportunities for improvement, ability to deal professionally with internal and external clients, Ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines, Innovative thinking and planning skills, Ability to function independently. \n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified. \n \nRequirements\nA degree in computer science, IT, or related field. Data engineering certification is a plus, with more than 5 experience as a data engineer/ETL Developer. \n \n \nClosing Date: 3 November 2023\n \nWork Level: Senior\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSENIOR ANALYST - INSURES SUPERVISION DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA0492\n \nPurpose of the Job:\nTo monitor compliance with insurance legislation, to conduct investigations relating to insurance business and to ensure a sound and efficient insurance industry. The person appointed to this position will report to the Manager.\n\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 Liaise with the public and other stakeholders when receiving complaints or enquiries;\n\u2022 Investigate complaints and enquires within the required departmental turnaround times;\n\u2022 Monitor compliance with legislation to ensure the protection and fair treatment of policyholders;\n\u2022 Participate in on-site inspections to insurers to establish compliance with insurance legislation; best practice and market conduct related issues;\n\u2022 Manage relationships with insurers assigned in the portfolio; \n\u2022 Perform administrative and other activities relating to the regulatory framework as may be required; and\n\u2022 Assist the department with projects that the department is working on. \n\n\nOther Key Competencies:\n \nThe candidate must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: A high level of judgement and a confident and decisive approach; problem analysis, information gathering, communication skills, good interpersonal skills and emotional intelligence, customer relations, persuasion skills and must be computer literate.  \n\n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified. \n \nRequirements\nA B. Com or law degree with at least 5 years relevant work experience in the insurance industry. Sound knowledge and understanding of the Insurance Acts and the insurance industry related operational requirements are essential. A Compliance and/or Risk Management background is essential. \n \nClosing Date: 3 November 2023\n \nWork Level: Skilled\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nMANAGER - COMPLAINTS AND QUERY RESOLUTIONS BUSINESS CENTRE DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA468\n \nDescription\nPurpose of the Job: \nTo provide and manage the activities of the Business Centre Complaints and Queries team, which include but not limited to the following: handling of complaints from multiple sources, redirecting of complaints to external regulatory authorities and internal FSCA divisions in accordance with relevant protocols and management of the debarment register. The person appointed to this position will report to the Departmental Head.\n\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 Oversee and manage the complaints and query resolution unit within the Business Centre;\n\u2022 Assist with the development, implementation and maintenance of the appropriate internal policies; \n\u2022 Implement and over the implementation of the Complaints and Queries Framework;\n\u2022 Engage with internal and external stakeholders with regards to the activities of the Unit;  \n\u2022 Manage the human resources of the team effectively and efficiently (train, monitor, lead, development and maintenance of performance standards for the team);\n\u2022 Assist in managing the department\u2019s business plan and budget in line with FSCA guidelines;\n\u2022 Attend to administrative and managerial responsibilities of the department as directed by the Departmental Head;\n\n\u2022 Manage the processes of referral of matters that do not fall within the scope of the FSCA to external stakeholders; \n\u2022 Prepare monthly trend analyses reports on matters handled by the Unit;\n\u2022 Manage, monitor and update the register of debarred representatives; and\n\u2022 Engage with key internal and external stakeholders to facilitate the closure of various matters and ensure adherence to service level agreements.\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nThe candidate must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: A high level of judgement, confidence and decisive approach, effective communication skills, show a high level of judgement, the ability to analyse problems, the ability to gather information, problem solving and the ability to work under pressure, be able to interact effectively with senior staff, industry partners and stakeholders, and organise, lead and motivate a team in order to meet individual and work group goals, ability to work effectively under pressure whilst upholding an emphasis on quality.\n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified.\n \nRequirements\nA Bachelor\u2019s Degree in law or Commerce. The candidate must have proven relevant and practical experience of at least 5 years within a financial services industry. A good understanding of the overall mandate of the FSCA and the various financial sector laws is required. \n \nClosing Date: 3 November 2023\n \nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nJUNIOR ANALYST - RETIREMENT FUND CONDUCT SUPERVISION DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: 268\n \nDescription\nPurpose of the Job: \nTo assist the department in supervising and monitoring of retirement funds, including funds under curatorship, statutory management and funds where boards have been appointed in terms of section 26(2) of the Pension Funds Act, 1956 (\u201cPF Act\u201d). The person will also conduct on-site inspections and reviews of retirement funds and assist with monitoring and evaluation of reporting and relief from appointment of section 26 trustees. The person will also be required to monitor and supervise administrators licensed in terms of 13B of the PF Act. The person appointed to this position will report to the Manager.\n\n\nKey Performance Areas:\nAssess complaints and queries received by the Department;\nOverseeing the appointment, monitoring and evaluation of reporting and relief from appointment of section 26 trustees;\nOn-site inspections and reviews of retirement funds;\nReport writing;\nAnalysis of statutory returns submitted by administrators licensed in terms of section 13B of the PF Act;\nAdditional special projects relating to the conduct supervision of retirement funds.\n\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nCandidates must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: A high level of judgement and a confident and decisive approach; problem analysis; information gathering; report writing; communication skills; good interpersonal skills and emotional intelligence; attention to detail; customer relations and persuasiveness skills. \n \nRequirements\nA Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Law with applicable experience. Good knowledge and exposure of the PF Act will be an added advantage.\n \nClosing Date: 27 October 2023\n \nWork Level: Junior\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSPECIALIST ANALYST - MARKETS, ISSUERS AND INTERMEDIARIES DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA1115\n \nPurpose of the Job\nThe Markets, Issuers and Intermediaries Department of the FSCA is responsible for licensing and supervising market infrastructures \n(i.e exchanges) operating within the South African financial markets in terms of the Financial Markets Act, 2012 (Act no 19 of 2012). \nThe department has oversight responsibilities over public markets, authorised users and issuers. The person appointed to this position \nwill be stationed in the Market Integrity and Decision Sciences Division and will report to the Manager.\n\n\nKey Performance Areas\n\u2022 Assist in identifying shortcomings and anomalies to the regulatory framework;\n\u2022 Assist in proposing changes to the regulatory framework and assist the Department with the implementation of such changes;\n\u2022 Assist to develop and maintain an effective and efficient supervisory framework within the context of the approved legislation;\n\u2022 Assist with the monitoring of compliance with the provisions of the Financial Markets Act and subordinate legislation;\n\u2022 Assist to plan and conduct inspections;\n\u2022 Liaise with and render appropriate regulatory guidance to stakeholders after consultation with the Manager and Head of Department.\n\u2022 Assist in conducting investigations regarding Market Infrastructures and to ensure that all relevant complaints are dealt with; and\n\u2022 Apply risk assessments and risk management techniques.\n\nOther Key Competencies:\nThe applicant must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: strong analytical abilities, attention to detail, leadership skills, active listening, critical thinking, strong financial and numeracy skills, excellent communication skills (verbal and written), ability to work in a team, Ability to work independently with minimal supervision, innovative and strategic thinking. Good understanding of market infrastructures operating within the South African Financial Markets and excellent project management skills. The candidate must be confident and decisive, approaching all tasks in a professional manner.\n\nThe FSCA is committed to increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its transformation strategy. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified.\n \nClosing Date: 27 October 2023\n \nRequirements\nA business, economics, accounting, Finance or Mathematics degree or similar with at least 5 years of experience in the financial sector and/or the regulatory environment within the financial services industry. The candidate must also demonstrate good knowledge of corporate governance frameworks, an understanding of financial markets, financial instruments and the mechanics of Market Infrastructures. Good knowledge and experience in financial analysis and risk management are essential.  \n \nWork Level: Mid-Level\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSENIOR MANAGER: ENFORCEMENT DEPARTMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA603\n \nPurpose of the Job\nTo lead and manage a team of investigators and assistant investigators that are responsible for investigating contraventions of financial sector laws and executing all concomitant enforcement decisions. The appointed person will report to the Departmental Head: Enforcement Department.\n\n\nKey Performance Areas:\n\u2022 To provide ongoing advice, guidance, and quality review of documents to enable subordinates to effectively perform their functions. To mentor, empower,   upskill, and develop subordinates to reach full potential.\n\u2022 Manage and proper oversight over investigations conducted by team.\n\u2022 Manage and proper oversight over enforcement process.\n\u2022 Quality review- review and quality control all reports, recommendations, and decisions with specific reference to correct outcomes.\n\u2022 Productivity of team-ensure that work delivered by the team is of high-quality standard and on time.\n\u2022 Team leadership- ensure that all staff in own area are skilled and empowered to perform their functions. \n\u2022 Identify and implement methods to improve efficiency and quality. \n\u2022 Conduct biannual performance appraisals.\n\n\nOther Key Competencies\nThe candidate must demonstrate good managerial and leadership skills. Good interpersonal and emotional intelligence. Effective written and verbal communication. Ability to think innovatively and strategically. Ability to work effectively under pressure. Analytical thinking. Problem-solving. Quality oriented. Attention to detail. Project management. Computer literacy.\n\n\nFSCA is committed towards increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its Employment Equity Plan. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified.\n \nClosing Date: 27 October 2023\n \nRequirements\nAn LLB or BCom degree or similar qualification. With at least 10 -15 years\u2019 experience in investigation, litigation, prosecution, evidence gathering, drafting of pleadings and presentation of cases. And 3- 5 years\u2019 management experience will be an added advantage. Technical knowledge of investigation techniques, rules of evidence, financial sector laws the FSCA is responsible for and the functioning of the system of financial regulation in SA.\n\nWork Level: Management\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "DEMAND AND ACQUISITION SPECIALIST - SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT (PRETORIA)\nReference Number: FSCA 65\n \nPurpose of the Job\nThe successful applicant will drive the sourcing of goods and services for the FSCA through the application of the total cost of ownership approach in compliance with legislation and detailed procurement policy in order to optimise supply chain variables of cost, quality, service and reliability. The person appointed in this role will report to the Departmental Head: Supply Chain.\n \nKey Performance Areas\n\u2022 Build and maintain relationships with end-users and service departments, follow up on escalated invoices and FSCA adheres to the National Treasury \n   rules with respect to payment of invoices.\n\u2022 Analyse past procurement information to understand historic sourcing trends and end user activities.\n\u2022 Provide advisory service to internal clients on planning and sourcing matters.\n\u2022 Provide feedback on technical issues and complex interventions in sourcing related matters.\n\u2022 Conduct systematic assessment of suppliers, assets and capabilities with respect to overall business strategy and ensure effective implementation \n  of the sourcing plan in order to meet project timelines.\n\u2022 Review, consider and approve new service providers on the vendor relationship management system.\n\u2022 Conduct industry and market analysis of goods and services to be procured (e.g. EME, SMME, QSE, etc.) and implement preferential procurement/ BEE     objectives during quotations processes.\n\u2022 Manage and monitor supplier relationship and performance and engage suppliers on poor performance with relevant stakeholders.\n\u2022 Analyse specifications to ensure clarity, weighting and scoring of criteria, and compliance with legislative requirements.\n\u2022 Monitor compliance to internal processes with SCM policy and prescripts and advice internal stakeholders.\n\u2022 Assist to ensure that the Terms of Reference (TOR) or Specifications are in accordance with the relevant prescripts, policies and procedures.\n\u2022 Provide relevant information and reports to SCM Management regarding sourcing matters.\n\u2022 Draft, update and manage the department\u2019s risk register.\n\u2022 Continuously monitor risks and threats that affect the supply chain management processes and systems.\n\u2022 Assist in other duties as requested by the Departmental Head: SCM and Senior Manager: SCM.\n\nOther Key Competencies\nThe applicant must demonstrate the following skills and attributes: Relationship Building, planning and organising, Problem Solving, \naction orientation, innovation, quality orientation, customer centric, analytical thinking and attention to detail, excellent communication skills \n(verbal and written), innovative and strategic thinking. The candidate must have the ability to establish priorities and manage several tasks. \nThe candidate must also demonstrate the ability to work effectively under pressure and in a professional manner.  \n\n\nThe FSCA is committed to increasing the representation of marginalised groups in line with its transformation strategy. Persons with disabilities are encouraged to apply. Please note that correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short listed candidates and that the FSCA reserves the right not to appoint if a suitable candidate is not identified. \n \nRequirements\nThe applicant must hold a Matric certificate plus a National Diploma or Bachelor\u2019s degree in Logistics, Finance/ Accounting/ Supply Chain Management or equivalent qualification with at least 3 to 5 years\u2019 relevant experience in Procurement. Must also have solid knowledge of the Public Finance Management Act, Preferential Procurement Framework Act and Treasury Regulations, including National Treasury SCM Instructions.\n \nClosing Date: 27 October 2023\n \nWork Level: Senior\nJob Type: Permanent\nSalary: Market Related\nEE Position: Yes\nLocation: Pretoria\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
